column1: OMAP-10 Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Palatine Tonsil with MACSima

column2: Werner Müller; Silvia Rüberg; Andreas Bosio
Andrea J. Radtke; Ellen M. Quardokus

column24: rationale
CD15 is expressed on neutrophils, eosinophils, and some monocytes. It is also expressed on Hodgkin-Reed-Sternberg cells. It is not an essential marker for the tonsil OMAP.

Alpha smooth muscle actin defines the fibroblastic reticular network and vasculature of the tonsil. This is an essential marker for many cell types including smooth muscle cells and many subsets of fibroblasts. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD11c is expressed on dendritic cells. It does not define a particular region in the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

BCL2 represents an anti-apoptotic protein highly expressed in mantle zone B cells and follicular lymphoma tumor B cells. This marker can be used to define the mantle zone (high expression) and germinal center (negative) in the tonsil. This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD138 is a marker for plasma cells along with the Plasma Cell and CD79a markers. Most plasma cells are located in the extra follicular region of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP. CD138 also defines the epithelium of the tonsil.
CD1c is expressed on mantle zone B cells and myeolid DC. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD279 (PD-1) is expressed on germinal center T cells.  This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD209 (DC-SIGN) defines DC-SIGN+ macrophages and dendritic cells.  This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD39 is expressed on T cells and endothelial cells in the tonsil. This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD19 is expessed on B cells (like CD20). CD20 is the prioritized marker for the tonsil OMAP. CD19 is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD4 is expressed by subsets of T cells. This marker is also expressed on a subset of myeloid cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD3 defines T cell zone and is an essential marker of T cells. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD21 defines follicular dendritic cell meshworks in primary follicles, secondary follicles, and germinal centers. This marker is essential for defining follicular dendritic cells and represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD68 cannot be used to define a specific anatomical structure but is expressed by many subsets of myeloid cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD20 is expressed on  B cells and defines B cell follicles This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD27 is expressed at differing levels on memory B cells, a fraction of plasma cells, and on naive and memory T cells, but is not expressed on naive B cells or effector T cells. It is also expressed on NK cells. This marker is not a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD79a is an antigen highly expressed by plasma cells.  In this panel, CD138 and the Plasma Cell marker are strongly expressed on plasma cells. Most plasma cells are located in the extra follicular region of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Collagen IV defines the capsule and extracellular matrix components of the tonsil. This marker is  a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD44 It is used to detect the activation status of many immune cell subsets. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
FoxP3  is expressed by T regulatory cells and T follicular regulatory cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD45 is expressed on all  hematopoietic cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP and can be used for downstream image analysis.
IgD defines naive B cells that are enriched in the mantle zones and primary follicles of the tonsil.  This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Cytokeratin Class II is expressed by the extracellular matrix. In the tonsil it defines the  tonsillar crypt. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

IgM is expressed in B cells. It is also secreted. Postive staining for IgM is not necesarily cell bound but can also represent deposited antibody. This marker does not represent a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
CD8  is expressed on the CD8 positive subset of T cells. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
HLA-DR is expressed on antigen presenting cells. It defines B cell follicles (HLA-DR+) and germinal centers (HLA-DR++).  This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

CD274 antibody detects the PD-1 protein (death receptor ligand) expressed on activated T cells, B cells, dendritic cells (DCs), antigen-presenting cells, keratinocytes, monocytes, and various types of tumor cells. It does not represent a priroritized target in tonsil OMAP.

Ki67  is expressed in the nucleus of proliferating cells. It defines dark zone (Ki67++) of the germinal center. This marker is essential for assessing cell division and proliferation. This marker represents a core panel and prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.

Plasma Cell is an antigen expressed by Plasma cells along with CD138 and CD79a. Most plasma cells are located in the extra follicular region of the tonsil. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
Vimentin defines stromal network of tonsil and serves as a pan-mesenchymal cell marker. This marker represents a prioritized target in the tonsil OMAP.
